7. Conclusion and Future Work

This chapter has presented NeuroSync v4.0, a comprehensive and robustly validated BCI framework that systematically addresses the primary barriers to real-world translation. By integrating material science (RGOPU electrodes), advanced signal processing (WCBSI, Riemannian geometry), cutting-edge machine learning (TCFormer, KD-CORAL, ABAT), balanced multimodal fusion (Dual-Decoder GradReb), and intelligent shared autonomy (Bayesian copilot), we have defined a path toward a new class of assistive neurotechnology. The performance metrics and architectural decisions are grounded in the latest peer-reviewed literature, providing a solid foundation for future clinical validation and deployment. Future work will focus on the proposed 30-subject clinical trial and the formal regulatory pathway through the FDA's Breakthrough Devices Program.

