Appendix A: Mathematical Foundations and Proofs

This appendix provides the complete mathematical derivations, proofs, and formal justifications for the core algorithms employed in NeuroSync v4.0.

A.1 Euclidean Alignment (EA) Whitening Proof

Theorem A.1 (EA Whitening Property). Let \{\mathbf{X}_i\}_{i=1}^{M} be a set of M EEG trials, where each \mathbf{X}_i \in \mathbb{R}^{N_c \times T} with N_c channels and T time samples. Define the reference covariance matrix as:

\bar{\mathbf{R}} = \frac{1}{M} \sum_{i=1}^{M} \frac{1}{T-1} \mathbf{X}_i \mathbf{X}_i^\top

Assume \bar{\mathbf{R}} is symmetric positive definite (SPD). The Euclidean Aligned trial is defined as \tilde{\mathbf{X}}_i = \bar{\mathbf{R}}^{-1/2} \mathbf{X}_i. Then the mean covariance of the aligned trials is the identity matrix:

\frac{1}{M} \sum_{i=1}^{M} \frac{1}{T-1} \tilde{\mathbf{X}}_i \tilde{\mathbf{X}}_i^\top = \mathbf{I}_{N_c}

Proof.

\begin{aligned}
\frac{1}{M} \sum_{i=1}^{M} \frac{1}{T-1} \tilde{\mathbf{X}}_i \tilde{\mathbf{X}}_i^\top &= \frac{1}{M} \sum_{i=1}^{M} \frac{1}{T-1} (\bar{\mathbf{R}}^{-1/2} \mathbf{X}_i)(\bar{\mathbf{R}}^{-1/2} \mathbf{X}_i)^\top \\
&= \bar{\mathbf{R}}^{-1/2} \left( \frac{1}{M} \sum_{i=1}^{M} \frac{1}{T-1} \mathbf{X}_i \mathbf{X}_i^\top \right) \bar{\mathbf{R}}^{-1/2} \\
&= \bar{\mathbf{R}}^{-1/2} \bar{\mathbf{R}} \bar{\mathbf{R}}^{-1/2} \\
&= \mathbf{I}_{N_c}
\end{aligned}

where we use the symmetry of \bar{\mathbf{R}}^{-1/2}. \square

This property ensures that the feature distributions from different subjects or sessions are centered and have comparable scale, thereby mitigating domain shift.

