Appendix D: Algorithm Pseudocode

D.1 Predictive CQI Computation

```
Algorithm: PredictiveCQI(EEG_buffer, fs=500)

Input: 32-channel EEG buffer of 1 second (500 samples)
Output: CQI vector, predicted time-to-failure for each channel

for each channel k in 1..32:
    # Component 1: Noise proxy (50 Hz)
    x_filtered_50 = bandpass(x_k, 48, 52, fs)
    N_k = rms(x_filtered_50)
    x_filtered_sig = bandpass(x_k, 1, 40, fs)
    S_k = rms(x_filtered_sig)
    CQI_noise = S_k / (S_k + N_k)
    
    # Component 2: Variance stability
    sigma2_short = variance(x_k[-2*fs:])  # last 2 seconds
    sigma2_long = variance(x_k[-30*fs:])  # last 30 seconds
    CQI_var = exp(-abs(sigma2_short - sigma2_long) / sigma2_long)
    
    # Component 3: Baseline drift
    t = linspace(0, 10, 10*fs)
    b_k = linear_regression_slope(t, x_k[-10*fs:])
    CQI_drift = exp(-abs(b_k) / 0.5)  # theta_drift = 0.5 µV/s
    
    # Scalar CQI (geometric mean)
    CQI_scalar = (CQI_noise * CQI_var * CQI_drift)^(1/3)
    
    # Update CQI history (60 samples at 1 Hz)
    CQI_history[k].append(CQI_scalar)
    if len(CQI_history[k]) > 60:
        CQI_history[k].pop(0)
    
    # Linear trend prediction
    if len(CQI_history[k]) == 60:
        t_pred = arange(60)
        a, b = linear_regression(t_pred, CQI_history[k])
        if a < 0:  # degrading
            t_fail = (0.4 - b) / a  # theta_bad = 0.4
            if t_fail < 120:
                warning("Channel %d degrading: predicted failure in %d seconds", k, t_fail)
```

D.2 WCBSI fNIRS Artifact Correction

```
Algorithm: WCBSI_Correction(OD_signal, fs=25, IMU_motion_energy)

Input: Optical density signal OD ∈ ℝ^{N_ch} for 4 channels, IMU energy E_motion
Output: Corrected HbO and HbR signals

# Stage 1: Motion artifact detection
for each channel k:
    # Wavelet decomposition (db4, J=4 levels)
    coeffs = wavedec(OD_k, 'db4', level=4)
    artifact_flag = False
    
    # Kurtosis test on detail coefficients
    for level j in 1..4:
        d_j = coeffs[level]
        kurt_j = kurtosis(d_j)
        if kurt_j > 3.0:
            artifact_flag = True
            break
    
    if E_motion > 0.5 or artifact_flag:
        # Stage 2: Artifact correction
        # Identify artifact type
        derivative = diff(OD_k)
        spike_indices = where(abs(derivative) > 3*std(derivative))
        
        if len(spike_indices) < 5:  # Type A: transient spike
            # Wavelet thresholding
            lambda_j = 3.0 * IQR(d_j)
            d_j_corrected = d_j * (abs(d_j) < lambda_j)
            OD_corrected = waverec(coeffs_corrected, 'db4')
        else:  # Type B/C: baseline shift or combined
            # Spline interpolation on artifact segment
            t_on, t_off = detect_artifact_bounds(OD_k)
            baseline_pre = mean(OD_k[t_on-25:t_on])
            baseline_post = mean(OD_k[t_off:t_off+25])
            spline_fit = cubic_spline([t_on, t_off], [baseline_pre, baseline_post])
            OD_corrected = OD_k - spline_fit(arange(len(OD_k)))
            
            # Apply wavelet thresholding on residual if needed
            coeffs = wavedec(OD_corrected, 'db4', level=4)
            for level j:
                coeffs[level] = coeffs[level] * (abs(coeffs[level]) < 3.0*IQR(coeffs[level]))
            OD_corrected = waverec(coeffs, 'db4')
        
        OD_k = OD_corrected
    
    # Convert OD to HbO/HbR via Modified Beer-Lambert Law
    HbO_k, HbR_k = beer_lambert(OD_k)
    
    # Stage 3: CBSI correlation enforcement
    r = pearsonr(HbO_k[-125:], HbR_k[-125:])  # last 5 seconds
    if r > 0:
        HbO_final = (HbO_k - HbR_k) / 2
        HbR_final = (HbR_k - HbO_k) / 2
    else:
        HbO_final = HbO_k
        HbR_final = HbR_k
    
    return HbO_final, HbR_final
```

D.3 Bayesian Goal-Inference Copilot

```
Algorithm: BayesianGoalInference(arm_state, object_list, belief_prior)

Input: Current end-effector position p_ee, velocity v_ee, list of M objects G = {g_1..g_M} with positions p_m, prior belief b_prior
Output: Updated belief b_posterior, AI command u_AI

# Likelihood computation
for each goal m in 1..M:
    direction_to_goal = (p_m - p_ee) / norm(p_m - p_ee)
    if norm(v_ee) > epsilon:
        direction_of_motion = v_ee / norm(v_ee)
        phi_m = arccos(dot(direction_of_motion, direction_to_goal))
    else:
        phi_m = pi/2  # no motion, uniform likelihood
    
    # Gaussian likelihood with sigma_phi = 0.4 rad (~20°)
    likelihood_m = exp(-phi_m^2 / (2 * 0.4^2))

# Bayes update
b_unnormalized = likelihood * b_prior
b_posterior = b_unnormalized / sum(b_unnormalized)

# Goal-conditioned AI command
b_max = max(b_posterior)
if b_max > 0.70:
    goal_idx = argmax(b_posterior)
    p_goal = G[goal_idx].position
    
    # Attractive potential field toward goal
    u_AI = K_goal * (p_goal - p_ee) / norm(p_goal - p_ee)
    
    # Add grasp refinement for object class
    object_class = G[goal_idx].class
    u_refine = precomputed_grasp_approach(object_class, p_goal)
    u_AI = u_AI + u_refine
else:
    # No confident goal: trajectory smoothing only
    u_AI = smooth_trajectory(v_ee)

# Update blending factor with goal confidence
rho = sigmoid(kappa1*(CLI - C_th) + kappa2*Phi_prox + kappa3*Phi_safe - kappa4*b_max)

# Final command
u_final = rho * u_human + (1 - rho) * u_AI
return u_final, b_posterior
```

